title: Ings' England Debut May Increase Costs
text:
Ings' England Debut May Increase Costs 12:33, UK, Tuesday 13 October 2015 Liverpool will have to pay more for Danny Ings than they originally hoped to, according to Sky sources. 
Sky Sports understands Burnley are now expecting higher compensation for the 23-year-old following his England debut. 
The Championship club have been holding out for Â£12m after Ings moved to Liverpool in the summer as a free agent. 
As Ings is under 24 years old, Burnley are entitled to compensation, but no date for the Professional Football Compensation Committee to settle the matter has been set. 
But add-ons may now increase after his international appearance in England's 3-0 victory over Lithuania. 
Ings has scored three times for Liverpool in just eight appearances for the club this season. Promoted Stories
